lead_paragraph: More than half the damage found along Northern California's levees after floods in January will not be repaired before the possible onslaught of El Nino this winter, according to United States Army Corps of Engineers documents. In fact, the damage may never be repaired unless there is more flooding, The Oakland Tribune reported today.
abstract: US Army Corp of Engineers says more than half damage to Northern California's levees that was caused by floods in January 1997 will not be repaired before possible onslaught of El Nino in coming winter (S)

headline.main: Levees May Not Be Fixed Before El Nino
